ratings.rComments: He's a tough teacher but very helpful and readily available if you meet him halfway. If you don't attend lectures or office hours, he will probably be much less friendly come crunch time. No official textbook, but he compiles his class notes into a book that is requried

I had Dr Keane for TAM 435, intermed fluid mech. Dr. Keane was fantastic at explaining the mathematics and practical laboratory application of fluid mechanics.  Funny, kind, and helpful, he is a rare instructor that is both likeable and challenges you to succeed. Introduced me to Tritton's "Phys. Fluid Dyn.", my favorite "causal reading" fluids ref

Don't buy the notes, just take your own in class. Also, go to class. He will literally tell you everything that will be on every exam. Very few students attended, which is why attendees easily get 90+% on exams and the average is 60%. Keane is clear, helpful, and doesn't take himself too seriously. Just go to every lecture and you'll get an A+.

I'd say Keane's exams are fair.  That being said, lectures were useless seeing as he basically reads the notes that he's already written and made you buy from the bookstore.  At least 211 was easy, 335 is actually complicated so it makes it worse.

The content in the class is easy, but Keane is always ready to screw up your grade - our final exam was way more difficult than it should have been, and he is quite possibly the meanest professor that I've ever dealt with

Going to class really helps if you decide to pay attention. All the people here saying you dont have to go to class probably didnt get an A. If you do the homework without just getting solutions and do the previous tests then you might get an A. He doesnt curve and his tests are worth a huge percent of the grade.Also his rubric is tough (94% for A)
Not interesting and is very rude. When asked about a misgrading on my exam, he refused to talk to me.
No comment

He definitely knows the materials, but not the way to teach it. He uses projector to teach the class, and spend most time doing monotonous teaching. He often ignores people who raise their hands. The lecture is really boring, it makes you wan to sleep.
Keane is one of a kind, lectures will put you to sleep but the notes help. Study in groups, but overall the class isn't bad. Just do the homework and make sure you understand it.

Terribly boring and his website is extremely unorganized. None of the practice tests had answers. Very repetitive in class. Monotone Australian voice. 90% of the class was test grades. all in all, I hated this class
I had keane as both my lecturer and Lab TA. He performs much better in small settings. Talk to him and you'll do fine
Lectures are very boring but he does present the material fairly clearly. Get help at Grainger if you are having trouble.

Prof. Keane has a reputation as being boring or teaching directly from his notes, but he is an excellent teacher. He has years of experience that help him address classes as a whole group, yet at the same time he is approachable if you need individual help. This isn't the first time I've had Keane but I definitely enjoyed this course more than 211

8 o'clock lecture was a true pain. Most people only showed up for the exams. As others have mentioned, all he does is go over his lecture notes. I found my TA to be more helpful. I kept on getting the impression that he was jaded and grumpy. He also made mean but understandable comments in class. Midterms were ridiculously easy. Final was alright.

Lecture is a joke, all he does is go over what is already written in his notes (which you can buy). Homework takes a long time and only 6 problems. Exams aren't to bad if you know what to do. But the final was terrible!

Lecture's don't help much, but his lecture notes and resources online help a lot. Draw a Free Body Diagram and sum forces and moments to zero and you're golden. Seriously, you'll get at least a B. He's not a bad guy, and his expectations are realistic.

As far as I know, he is the only TAM 210/211 prof. Either way I didn't find him to be too bad. Lost of time spent on HW. Exams are only two problems but you should know what to expect from the HW. Make sure you take advantage of your TA if you are stumped otherwise you will have trouble. Work hard and study and you will do well.

I could not stay awake in that class (8AM). Partly because it was early, partly because Keane is not intent on making the class interesting, or lecturing at all for that matter. He can be helpful 1 on 1 (albeit sarcastic). Some people love his humor. I did not find it amusing.

The book is crystal clear, Keane is not. Lectures were often COMPLETELY useless. Homework was really time-consuming. He's good at answering questions when they're specific, the hard part is thinking of a question that isn't "explain all of that again." I don't think he has any place teaching. Not a hard class though. But tests are weighted heavily.

I've had Keane twice now, for 211 and 212. Let me say that he's not as bad as his reputation may suggest. Lectures can be pretty pointless, but when exam time comes he always goes through worked examples that help. Exams are hard but predictable, just go to office hours. I've also never seen Keane yell at anyone in class, he's actually pretty nice.

Absolutely horrible teacher. Only went to lecture to turn in homework. He has a terribly disorganized Compass page with tests without solutions, or with wrong answers. I typed in an integral he did by hand on a practice final on my calculator and he was wrong. If you can avoid him, definitely do. Use the textbook to learn, he doesn't teach.

Keane is pretty boring I'll say, and he lectures are pretty useless at times.  The trick is using the textbook and the lecture notes he has you buy.  Make sure you do attend class often though, because this is how you'll get a feel for what he wants on his tests.  Put in the time, and you'll score well.
His lectures are extremely boring. It's better to just work the material on your own. He has a negative attitude toward students (and TA's and... everyone) so do not expect any flexibility.

If you're a student who wants to attend class and wants to learn, he's the best teacher you'll find. He's helpful, if he knows you're interested. But if you want to fool around, you probably don't want to mess with him.

The absolute WORST and RUDEST teacher ever in U of I. He has the reputation of yelling at students without any reason. Lectures were pointless to go to. Working on your own would be a much better idea. AVOID HIM IF YOU CAN!

This professor is probably one of the worst that i have ever had. His lectures are so pointless and boring. Only about 1/3 of the class actually attends lecture because they're so useless. His exams aren't too bad, but he grades pretty tough. ONE OF THE WORST CLASSES I'VE EVER TAKEN AT UIUC!

Spends lecture doing examples that are already worked out in the textbook he makes you buy so there is no real reason to go to lecture. He's very hard to meet up with and seems to try to avoid students as much as possible. The class is fairly simple but DO NOT CHEAT ON ANY HOMEWORK. He drops 10% of your grade for copying one problem.
Terrible professor, examples are poorly done and the grading is tough.
Believe me. Skip all lectures and go to discussions. TAs explain concepts much much better than him. Sorry but that's true.

He is really a horrible teacher. I would advise you to skip lecture bc half of it is him taking about Australia. He is very rude and not approachable. He is the kind of teacher that is only at college to do research not help students. His TAM 210 final exam was extremely difficult, and grades never posted. Expect your posted grades to be very late.
Don't like the lectures cuz it's just sooooo boring. Don't like Keane's attitude, either. Tests are long so make sure you practice beforehand. Past exams : must do!

Any teacher that keeps boxes of student tests and homework assignments outside his office in the hallway 24/7 is not a good teacher to begin with.  The class material is very easy. He doesnt teach well but test are fair/simple, helpful in office hours. Gave students 10% off ENTIRE grade for use of Cramster on ONE HW prob. Be prepared foraroughfinal

Even after getting an A+ for the class, I have to say he is NOT approachable by students. I dont know why he has an attitude toward those who stayed after class to ask him questions. however, he does tell you what to study for on the exams so that was helpful. but otherwise, he is rude!

Professor is incredibly rude and intolerable during office hours and otherwise too.  I don't know what keeps him in such a constant bad mood but beware of his outrageous temper at the most random times.  Even if you treat him with respect, he will spit at you.  Final exam is just his way of taking out his unhappiness in life onto students.
Worst class ever. Lectures are the most boring thing in the world and exams are crazy hard and long.

Useless. Absolutely useless. Horrible teaching style, has unfair expectations and gets angry when his monotonous Australian accent lulls everyone to sleep. Childish and immature when approached by students. Does not believe any reason for any exam conflicts (even for citizenship tests). I have an A so I'm not biased. Ask ANYONE who took this course

He is terrible. He spends most of his lectures talking about how Australian words mean diff things. Also he is such a child. Our final exam was the hardest exam I have ever taken. He found out that our text book was located on cramster and took the hardest problems he could and used them for the final. There is no curve bc the Q's were on cramster

He was my lab coordinator, yet he made it to 80% of the labs (which is much much higher than any other lab I've ever had).  Always there to answer questions and give hints.  He may not be great as a prof. (I wouldn't know) but if you can get him in lab, do it.

This is my second semester in a row with the prof. He definitely grows on you. His teaching slides are outdated (he uses transparencies) but he is well versed in what he teaches and gets to the point. You have to go to class to get a good grade and he makes not of who goes. Great professor.

Hardly approachable.  I went in to get an exam and his first words were "You're lucky I'm in a better mood today than I was yesterday," went on a rant about students cheating, and then called the head TA "stupid" and "an idiot" for her telling us we could come in and get our exams from him. Totally inappropriate! And I'm hardly getting started...

Keane is not half bad at teaching but can be an arrogant aussie at times..  He insults students and thinks they're all dumb americans.  Don't go to his lectures or office hours but utilize your TA Office hrs for homework.. Also be weary of his final exam, its impossible

Keane is funny in lecture and does a decent job teaching. The hour exams and homework are all fairly easy, however the final was extremely hard and not curved. Keane is also extremely hostile towards students and not approachable outside of class.

Classes were easy in difficulty and the exams were easy. The final however was unfairly hard and just poor (avg of 70 with a SD of 20 and no curve). The man is crabby at best despite his good teaching skills. Take a course from him if you can learn on your own. Buy his notes too, they are good.

Great professor with crystal clear lectures. Everything he administers is fair, homework, exams, etc. If you read the book or go to lecture their is no reason why you can't get an A. Highly recommended professor to take.

Decent lecturer, did a lot of examples on the board which were pretty helpful. Notes packet is full of info, which saves you if you miss the early (8am) lecture. Exams are just 2-3 problems so you need to be careful not to make a mistake. Unfortunately, he's horrible at getting back to emails and communicating about conflicts, etc.
Very thorough explanations. I can see why some may have been taken aback by his comments in class, but lighten up. Good teacher, though the tests can really screw you over if you make a big mistake.

All his notes are legibly hand-written. Doesn't matter whether you go to class or not, but if you choose not to you'll miss a lot of things related to exams. Exams are not hard generally but getting a single question wrong can have deadly consequences.

He is a decent professor who explains things well, but a horrible human being. Has no regards for students' feelings. Is rude if you go to office hours and his explanation doesn't work. He also makes fun of individual students (calling a bunch of girls in the class not so very decent things) which is funny in the class but horribly wrong.

Very good lecturer and funny at times. He holds his own review sessions for the exams. However, exams tend to be long and poorly worded, except for the final. But the content is pretty straightforward.
Very thorough, although he often repeats himself. Can put you to sleep, but if you pay attention you will learn a lot. Always able to answer students' questions.
Keane is an awesome guy. You'll get used to his Australian accent and learn a ton from his lectures.
Great lecturer.

Class was pretty straightforward.  A lot of people didn't like him, but I enjoyed his class a lot.  "Take your notes to Murphy's and after every page turn take a drink, eventually your studying will become much more interesting."
Terrible.  Unfair old coot.

Conceited Australian. He constantly degrades America and its ways of teaching, and while others may find his remarks funny, I find them completely unnecessary. Do not go to his office hours unless you want to be chewed up and spit out.  Lectures are alright, but the material can be learned without them by reading the book.
Keane is great. Classic Aussie with a fantastic accent. "So you have a test here, ya see?"

Keane is a quite a character - Australian scientist who likes to drink a lot. Course notes were kinda worthless, and my TA was awful, so that didn't help. The concepts aren't hard if you go to his lectures and read the book. Overall, my only complaint is that he flys through the material at an almost overwhelming rate.

Awesome guy with a great Austrailian accent and great stories, but something about his voice puts everyone in the class to sleep.  He does examples the whole time, which is helpful but also pretty boring.  Go to class if you have him, sometimes he goes over homework problems in class and will be mad if you ask him about the same problems later.
Tedius at times, but very interesting side rants

Classes are usually pretty dry, but worth going to for his off-topic comments/descriptions of Australian drinking games. Do the past exams that he hands out in class and this class is a piece of cake.
No Comments
No Comments
Nice Aussie... no one goes to this class after awhile, but if you go and get to know him, he will totally help you out. Will help you anytime you need help.
Austrailian accent
Very Australian and very difficult.
